init_text: You're Barack Obama. 4 years into your retirement, you awake to find a letter with no return address on your bedside table. It reads "I hope you've had a chance to relax Barack...but pack your bags and call the number below. It's time to start the real job." Signed simply, "JFK."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: to be someone with a sense of humor, or at least some connection to you.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: It rings a few times, and a familiar voice answers.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: the voice of a man you haven't heard in years, but it's instantly recognizable.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: the former President of the United States, John F. Kennedy.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: that he needs your help, and that this is no joke.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "I am John F. Kennedy, sitting in front of my computer in the Oval Office.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You've got a gig at the Kennedy Center, and you're rehearsing.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: picks you up and drives you to the place.
